5.00








One-Touch Assurance
The latest innovation in wearables, Revolar’s only job is to help empower you to feel more safe and connected. Anytime you feel uncomfortable or think you might be in danger, simply press the Revolar button to send an alert to your pre-determined contacts—complete with your GPS location—so you can get the help you need.


Safety Made Simple
      Revolar connects to an app on your phone through Low Energy Bluetooth®. Load up to 5 contacts in the app, and if you ever feel unsafe or are in a situation where you need help, simply press your Revolar button for assistance. A quick double press will send a Yellow Alert to let your contacts know you need to get in touch with them, and a triple press will send a Red Alert to let them know you need professional help immediately.

Revolar Fits Your Lifestyle
        Unlike other wearables, Revolar believes in function over fashion. The Revolar button is sleek and discreet and can either be hidden under your clothing or clipped onto your keychain.









 Description & Guides


Lightweight. Powerful. Active.
Different alerts: A rapid double-press sends a Yellow Alert, indicating that you’re uncomfortable or need to get in touch with your contacts. A rapid triple-press sends a Red Alert, indicating that you need professional help.
GPS Link: Your Revolar contacts don't need to download the app—whenever you trigger an alert, a text message is sent to your contacts with an active GPS link.
Out of sight:Revolar is very discreet and measures less than 2 inches. It easily hides under your clothing or can be clipped onto your keychain.
Waterproof: Certified IP68, which means you can ditch the bag of rice if Revolar ends up in water.
Long battery life: Revolar uses a simple watch battery for power, which lasts up to a year.
Interchangeable: Revolar comes with two different cases: one to clip onto your clothing and one to attach to your keys.
One-touch assurance.
Revolar is the next innovation in wearables. Unlike wearables that track your steps or sleep, Revolar’s only job is to help empower you to feel more safe and connected. Anytime you feel uncomfortable or think you might be in danger, a quick double press will send a Yellow Alert (a triple press will send a Red Alert) to your pre-determined Revolar contacts—complete with your GPS location—so you can get the help you need.
Revolar connects to our app through Low Energy Bluetooth® technology. Once paired, you simply enter your Revolar Contacts, have a conversation about what the different alerts mean to you, and you’re good to go! The best part about Revolar is that it’s fully customizable.
Revolar fits your lifestyle.
Revolar takes care of all the complexity so you don’t have to. In an emergency situation you do not have time to use your phone. Calling for help with Revolar is as easy as pressing a button. In fact, it IS pressing a button.
Revolar is empowerment.
Unlike other wearbles, Revolar believes in function over fashion. The Revolar button is sleek and discreet and can either be hidden under your clothing or clipped onto your keychain.
Feel safer wherever you go—order your Revolar Wearable Safety Device from Brookstone today!
Can I use Revolar without my phone?
Because Revolar uses Bluetooth technology, your phone will need to be within Bluetooth range (typically 30 feet) and have a data or Wi-Fi connection in order to send alerts.
What kinds of alerts can I send with Revolar?
A two press “Yellow” alert typically indicates that you may be feeling uncomfortable or unsafe and would like to be contacted.

Three or more presses sends a “Red” alert that can indicate you may already be in danger and need urgent assistance.

In both alert cases, your Revolar contacts will be notified via text and/or email that you have sent an alert, and they will be provided with your location information until the alert is cancelled.


The Bluetooth® word mark and logos are registered trademarks owned by Bluetooth SIG, Inc. and any use of such marks by Brookstone is under license.




